      <h3>About College of Natural Resources</h3>
      <p>
        The College of Natural Resources (CNR), established in 1992 as the Natural Resources Training Institute, is a premier institution under the Royal University of Bhutan. Located in Lobesa, Punakha, CNR focuses on agriculture, rural development, and natural resources management, aligning its goals with Bhutan's vision of Gross National Happiness.
      </p>
      <p>
        The campus spans 98 acres on the eastern slope of Lobesa, approximately 63 km from Thimphu. CNR offers a serene environment conducive to learning, with facilities built in traditional Bhutanese architectural style.
      </p>
